time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1/2-inch-thick pieces.

Peel and mince @Garlic{1%clove}. Peel and mince @Ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

> Trim green beans if necessary or cut broccoli into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%TBSP} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add garlic and half the minced ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Swap in green beans or broccoli for carrots; roast 12-15 minutes for green beans or 15-20 minutes for broccoli.

While rice cooks, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion whites and remaining minced ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Miso Sauce Concentrate{1}, half the @Apricot Jam{1} (all for 4 servings), 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4), and a squeeze of lime juice to pan with aromatics. Cook, stirring, until combined and thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @Butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Taste and add more lime juice if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt.

Toss carrots with lime zest.

Divide rice, carrots, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with sauce and sprinkle everything with scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.